org.seedstack.business.api.domain.events

Class DomainEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.seedstack.business.api.domain.BaseValueObject
      • org.seedstack.business.api.domain.events.DomainEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<BaseValueObject>, DomainObject, ValueObject, Event, Producible
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BaseAggregateEvent

    public abstract class DomainEvent
extends BaseValueObject
implements Event
    BaseEvent is the abstract class to extend to create an event. It extends from BaseValueObject which provides equals and hashCode. This allows to check cyclic call detection and to test events with EventFixture.

    It is possible to directly implements Event instead of extends BaseEvent. But you will have to implements equals and hashCode.

    NB: Event should be immutable.

    Author:
    pierre.thirouin@ext.mpsa.com
